By virtue of which grant he is ready to prove that the manor carne to the hands of the Prior and he was thenceforth seised of the agistrnent in question. An inquiry is directed and the Jury find that all holders of the manor from time immemorial, likewise the Master of the Temple before the suppression of the Order, after the suppression Earl Thomas, his tenant John de Dalton, and the Priors from the date of the grant to them have without interruption agisted all manner of animals in the lands described and at pleasure taken the profits of the agistment. Judgment is given allowing the claim.
